# claude.arch.feedback
## Round 1 ‚Äî 2026-06-12 ‚Äî Architecture v1

Internal red team (decoupling, resilience, codebase-integration realist) + CLIs. Tally: **1 ADVANCE / 4 ANOTHER ROUND**.

## Decoupling reviewer ‚Äî ADVANCE (with fix)
- persist_research is a "god-aggregator" (maps/validates/hashes/looks-up/hands-off inline) ‚Üí introduce
  an ingestion/application service; keep the graph node a thin caller.
- tuple_key + canonicalize + value-equality are split across FactStore (column) and ConflictPolicy
  (pure fn) ‚Üí **extract a `FactIdentity` service** both consume. (Single most important fix.)
- "Pure" policy writing `lifecycle=superseded` couples policy to store columns. FactStore interface
  too broad (persist+query+conflict+evidence) ‚Äî SQLite-shaped.
- No port for entity/alias resolution; `canonicalize` is an un-ported seam; `confidence` has no owner.

## Resilience reviewer ‚Äî ANOTHER ROUND
- **No transaction boundary** across fact+evidence+fact_revision+conflict writes ‚Üí partial write =
  provenance-less facts (violates "every fact has evidence", P3). **The single most important fix.**
- No per-fact isolation: a malformed qualifier dict throwing during tuple_key hashing loses the whole
  run's facts (and persist_research "must never crash a completed run").
- Alias miss behavior undefined ‚Üí phantom entities (silent under-coverage) or dropped facts; need
  quarantine, never auto-create canonical.
- Validation can silently drop 100% of a property ‚Üí need a drop-rate guardrail.
- Spurious conflicts persist & block promotion with no auto-close; as_of null ordering undefined;
  no recompute when a registry tier changes; re-run dedup/idempotency undefined.

## Codebase-integration realist ‚Äî ANOTHER ROUND (code-verified)
- **THE BLOCKER:** "emit facts into ResearcherState, aggregate in persist_research" does NOT survive
  the graph. Researcher subgraph compiles with `output=ResearcherOutputState` (deep_researcher.py:754)
  = only {compressed_research, raw_notes} (state.py:123-127); supervisor_tools flattens
  compressed_research into a ToolMessage and concatenates raw_notes (string). No structured channel
  carries typed facts up. AgentState has no fact field; persist_research reads only raw_notes/
  final_report. ‚Üí must thread a typed reducer field through ResearcherState‚ÜíResearcherOutputState‚Üí
  SupervisorState‚ÜíAgentState + rewrite the supervisor fan-in, OR relocate extraction post-supervisor.
- **Evidence spans aspirational:** compress_research emits LLM prose (str-join, :716-726); no per-claim
  source binding survives; spans can be hallucinated. "no span‚Üíno fact" unenforceable without
  substring-verification against a retained, source-addressable note segment.
- Nested `qualifiers:{}` object-list schema is the HARD case for Gemini/Codex envelope coercion;
  existing structured outputs (KnowledgeAssessment, SubjectResolution) are flat scalars. Truncated
  list = invalid JSON, not "fewer facts".
- Underestimated: no migration framework (executescript ad hoc, :94-97); **no CLI entry point exists
  at all** (everything under `langgraph dev`) ‚Äî dossier show/compare/export is a net-new program.

## codex (CLI) ‚Äî ANOTHER ROUND
- Echoes: ingestion/application service; FactStore too broad; transaction/idempotency contract for
  insert+evidence+conflict+promotion+lifecycle+revision; per-fact validation + retry limits; SQLite
  single-writer + busy_timeout + bounded retry; evidence must be validated exact substring of a
  retained note; nested qualifiers not a real closed enum (validate each item post-coercion); new
  egress (model call ships source material ‚Äî provider retention); no soft-delete despite "schema-ready";
  registry version + deterministic recompute.

## gemini (CLI) ‚Äî ANOTHER ROUND
- **Single fix: define a formal `EntityResolver` port + adapter** ‚Äî tuple_key depends on instance_id;
  undefined alias‚Üícanonical mapping makes conflict detection (the core value) unreliable.
- SQLite write contention under concurrency; "no span‚Üíno fact" degrades to "fails-to-coerce‚Üídropped"
  silent data loss on Gemini/Codex; injecting the whole property_def enum per prompt may exceed
  context; evidence-store bloat (no retention/pruning).

### Convergence: ANOTHER ROUND (4/5). Consensus fixes for v2 below.

---

## Round 2 ‚Äî 2026-06-12 ‚Äî Architecture v2 convergence check

Internal red team + CLIs. Tally: **3 ADVANCE / 1 ANOTHER ROUND (integration realist) / gemini pending.**

- **Decoupling ‚Äî ADVANCE.** FactIdentity / pure-intents / writer-query split / ingestion service all
  CLOSED. Fold-in: pure policies must receive the current tuple's stored facts as INPUT and emit
  fully-resolved intents (Supersede/auto-close), so FactWriter only persists, never re-decides.
- **Resilience ‚Äî ADVANCE.** Atomic tx + per-fact isolation + alias-quarantine + auto-close + null
  ordering + recompute + dedup all CLOSED. Fold-in: the registry-bump **recompute pass needs the same
  atomic-tx + per-tuple isolation + resumable-on-registry_version** contract (the one mutating path not
  yet covered); source-tagged-notes drop = unrecoverable-in-run (detectable via drop-rate).
- **codex ‚Äî ADVANCE.** All 6 closed. Fold-ins: (1) cost is `sources √ó properties`, NOT "cohort√ó6" ‚Äî
  needs a per-run extraction ceiling/batching; (2) dedup must key on **canonical(value,unit)**, not raw
  value; (3) clarify no-op/deduped reruns write **no** fact_revision.
- **integration realist ‚Äî ANOTHER ROUND (code-verified):**
  - **Placement bug:** `extract_facts` is placed after `final_report_generation`, which **clears
    `notes`‚Üí[]** (final report node). So read **`raw_notes`** (survives), or insert before
    final_report_generation. Also note `persist_research` has TWO in-edges (answer_from_dossier +
    final_report_generation) ‚Äî extraction wires only on the research path.
  - **THE re-opened blocker:** "source-tagged notes" is NOT a small compression tweak. `raw_notes` is
    `list[str]` joined at compress_research and **re-joined at the supervisor fan-in (deep_researcher.py
    :487-490 `"\n".join`)**, destroying structure. Carrying `{source_url,text}` requires changing the
    type/reducer at ResearcherState + ResearcherOutputState + the supervisor flatten + AgentState ‚Äî the
    exact round-1 boundary. And tool results aren't source-tagged at that point (extract_sources greps
    URLs post-hoc) ‚Äî so a structured per-source carry from the search tools is needed. Span-verification
    (¬ß4) has no verbatim text to verify against until this survives line 488. **The round-1 blocker is
    open, not closed.**

### Convergence: ANOTHER ROUND. Real decision: how source-attributed text reaches extract_facts.

---

## Round 3 ‚Äî 2026-06-12 ‚Äî Architecture v3 convergence check

Internal red team + CLIs. Tally: **2 ADVANCE / 2 ANOTHER ROUND** (two code-verified blockers, fixed in v4).

- **Resilience+Decoupling ‚Äî ADVANCE.** Both round-2 fold-ins CLOSED (recompute atomic/resumable;
  policies receive stored facts, writer never re-decides). Fold-ins: run_source is a concurrent fan-out
  write table (not covered by the fact-writes single-writer claim) ‚Üí needs WAL/busy_timeout + retention/
  soft-delete + content-hash dedup; run_source write needs a port (not direct aiosqlite in tools);
  policies should read via a FactQuery DTO.
- **gemini ‚Äî ADVANCE.** Boundary blocker resolved; remaining (provenance pollution from extracting over
  discarded sources; density of one-call-per-source over many properties; storage redundancy) manageable
  at impl/prompt layer.
- **Integration realist ‚Äî ANOTHER ROUND (code-verified):** (1) **run_id doesn't exist at the tool
  layer** ‚Äî it's `lastrowid` from the persist_research INSERT (storage.py:159,218), minted AFTER tools
  run; only thread_id is in state (:940). Fix: preallocate run_id (or key by thread_id, reconcile).
  (2) **Only Tavily keeps per-source {url, raw_text}** (utils.py:84,120-131); CLI/native search return
  summarized prose ‚Üí run_source empty/low-fidelity, span-verification fails. Fix: per-adapter capture
  contract; unsupported adapters disable fact extraction.
- **codex ‚Äî ANOTHER ROUND:** same two blockers (run_id lifecycle inversion; per-adapter source capture).
  Plus: same-run conflicting facts won't see each other unless candidates are staged cumulatively before
  the batch write; the source ceiling must be deterministic + record incomplete-coverage (omitted
  sources mustn't make absence look authoritative).

### Disposition (v4 ‚Äî all incorporated, no user decision)
(a) Preallocate run_id at graph start (research_runs row status=running, finalized at persist).
(b) Per-adapter source capture: only raw-text adapters (Tavily-class) feed run_source; summarizing
adapters disable fact extraction (report still produced). (c) Cumulative same-run candidate staging ‚Äî
ingestion evaluates each tuple against stored facts AND the run's other candidates. (d) Deterministic
source ceiling + coverage-incomplete marker. (e) run_source via RunSourceStore write port, content-hash
dedup, soft-delete + prune, WAL+busy_timeout. (f) Policies read via FactQuery DTO. Provenance-pollution
+ density noted as impl/prompt concerns.

---

## Round 4 ‚Äî 2026-06-12 ‚Äî Architecture v4 convergence check

Internal red team + CLIs. Tally: **1 ADVANCE / 2 ANOTHER ROUND** (implementation-level seams; fixed in v5).

- **Resilience+Decoupling ‚Äî ADVANCE.** run_source write port + concurrency + FactQuery DTO CLOSED.
  Fold-ins: prune policy must not drop run_source still referenced by live evidence; stale-`running`
  orphan rows need a reaper; put soft_deleted_at on run_source DDL.
- **Integration realist ‚Äî ANOTHER ROUND (code-verified):** preallocation needs a **finalize UPDATE
  port** ‚Äî `save_run_and_upsert_subject`/`log_research_run` both INSERT complete rows (storage.py:197,
  138-159), so "finalized in persist_research" would create a 2nd row; need finalize_research_run(run_id)
  called by both research + cache paths. Entry is `assess_knowledge` (START edge :1040) which branches
  to the cache path, so a dedicated `preallocate_run` node on START‚Üíassess_knowledge is cleaner;
  subject_id NULL until finalize. **Per-run disable is wrong** ‚Äî get_all_tools can mix Tavily+CLI search;
  must be **per-source** (extract sources with a run_source row, skip others) + mark run coverage-incomplete.
- **codex ‚Äî ANOTHER ROUND:** same ‚Äî one authoritative run lifecycle (status field, graph-start INSERT,
  persist UPDATE/finalize, failure cleanup) + run-level extraction/coverage status defining mixed-adapter
  behavior; persisted coverage-incomplete marker; source ceiling marker not in ¬ß7.
- **gemini ‚Äî (pending; 4 reviews decisive.)**

### Disposition (v5 ‚Äî all incorporated, no user decision)
preallocate_run node on START‚Üíassess_knowledge (status='running'); finalize_research_run UPDATE port
called by both research + cache paths (one row per run); stale-running reaper; per-SOURCE extraction
(skip sources without a run_source row; mixed-adapter runs extract their raw-text sources);
persisted research_runs.coverage_incomplete; run_source.soft_deleted_at + prune guard (don't drop rows
referenced by live evidence). All implementation-level ‚Äî convergence is near.
